  *chuckle*<br>
<br>
However, I don't really think I need to.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
This pointless war cannot be un-made. But we urgently need to know that the invasion was not illegal as well. <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Looking over United Nations Resolutions 661, 678, 686, 687, 688, 707, 715, 986, 1284 and yes..1441..dating back to 6th, August, 1990..it can be seen that Iraq <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>never complied with the terms set before it to ensure the end of the first Gulf War</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.<br>
<br>
The most recent war was not illegal..nor was it even a new &quot;war&quot; in it's own right..because the 1991 Gulf war was never ended.<br>
